{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c61cc85d-5aa1-4aa2-a43a-a3169bafd92c","content":"Here are **3 performance anti-patterns** in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Recursive wildcard glob — `**\\*.*` (line 9, `.csproj`)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nThe `**\\*.*` glob forces MSBuild to walk the **entire directory tree** during evaluation. This is the single most common cause of slow evaluation. If the tree is large (e.g., `node_modules`, deep `obj` folders from other projects), it becomes extremely expensive. **Fix:** scope the glob to specific extensions or a known subdirectory.\n\n---\n\n### 2. File I/O via property function (line 13, `.csproj`)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nCalling `System.IO.File.ReadAllText` is **synchronous disk I/O executed during evaluation**—every restore, design-time build, and IDE reload pays this cost. Property functions should avoid file reads; prefer an MSBuild `ReadLinesFromFile` task at build time instead.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Three-level deep import chain (`imports/`)\n```\ncsproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nEach `<Import>` adds an evaluation pass. A 3-deep chain isn't catastrophic on its own, but it compounds with the issues above because **every import is re-evaluated on each pass**. Flattening or consolidating these would reduce overhead, especially in a solution with many projects sharing these props.\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** The recursive glob and the `ReadAllText` property function are the heaviest hitters. The nested import chain is a minor contributor that amplifies the other two. Addressing the glob and removing the evaluation-time file read would yield the biggest improvement.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9cbf35e1-ba15-41ef-ab64-14e4c03b6af2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a complete picture of the project. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues.","outputTokens":489},"id":"397d555e-5fb1-4cc5-a367-8e7532719728","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:10:04.683Z","parentId":"f2a9f3f4-d376-435b-83fd-3f18ca5f0687"}
